In this article, President Trump meets with escapees from North Korea in the Oval Office. The escapees share their stories of fleeing North Korea and their struggles living under the regime. They express their gratitude to President Trump for his attention to North Korea's human rights issues and ask for his help in stopping the repatriation of defectors from China. President Trump listens to their stories and thanks them for their bravery. The article also briefly mentions President Trump's remarks on the declassified memo sent to Congress, in which he calls it a "disgrace" and expresses his concern about the state of the country.